<item>
            <title>[SPARK-6330] newParquetRelation gets incorrect FileSystem</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-6330</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s a snippet from newParquet.scala:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    def refresh(): Unit = {&lt;br/&gt;
      val fs = FileSystem.get(sparkContext.hadoopConfiguration)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;      // Support either reading a collection of raw Parquet part-files, or a collection of folders&lt;br/&gt;
      // containing Parquet files (e.g. partitioned Parquet table).&lt;br/&gt;
      val baseStatuses = paths.distinct.map { p =&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        val qualified = fs.makeQualified(new Path(p))&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;        if (!fs.exists(qualified) &amp;amp;&amp;amp; maybeSchema.isDefined) &lt;/p&gt;
{
          fs.mkdirs(qualified)
          prepareMetadata(qualified, maybeSchema.get, sparkContext.hadoopConfiguration)
        }

&lt;p&gt;        fs.getFileStatus(qualified)&lt;br/&gt;
      }.toArray&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If we are running this locally and path points to S3, fs would be incorrect. A fix is to construct fs for each file separately.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
